`crates/` is the workspace root; its single member, `steno`, is the compiler for the stroke-annotated `.steno` DSL. Depending on `crates/` currently means depending on `steno` — there is no shared library code, workspace-level abstraction, or cross-crate protocol to track here yet.

Nothing spans multiple children because there is only one. All coupling, invariants, and pipeline details (parse → expand → render/snippet, corpus-driven test coverage, no-panic/`Result`-based contract, canonicalized stroke text via `render_stroke`) live entirely in `steno/rollup.ctx` and should be read there rather than restated.

No `intent.md` exists for this directory, so no divergence can be assessed.